  <brief_title>Open-lable Extension Study on Safety and Efficacy of Neramexane to Treat Congenital and Acquired Nystagmus</brief_title>
  <official_title>Long-term Open-label Extension Study to Assess the Safety, Tolerability, and Efficacy of Neramexane Mesylate in Congenital Idiopathic Nystagmus and Acquired Nystagmus</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Merz Pharmaceuticals GmbH</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Merz Pharmaceuticals GmbH</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate the long-term safety, tolerability and efficacy
      of neramexane mesylate in the treatment of congenital idiopathic nystagmus (CIN). In
      addition, a subgroup of multiple sclerosis (MS) patients suffering from acquired nystagmus
      will be included.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
